Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the rice.

When boiling, add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12%mins}.

Drain in a #sieve{} and pop back into the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Red Onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced).

Halve the @Green Pepper{1}(halved). Discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Roughly chop the @Coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Pop the @Diced Chicken Breast{260%g} into a #bowl{} with the @Cornflour{20%g}, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} then toss to coat.

Once the oil is hot, add the chicken to the frying pan and stir-fry until golden brown and cooked through, ~{8-10%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Sprinkle on the @Thai Style Spice Mix{1}. 

> TIP: Add less if you don't like too much heat.

When the chicken is cooked, add the red onions and peppers. Stir-fry until softened, ~{2-3%mins}.

Lower the heat and stir in the @Hoisin Sauce{64%g}, @Soy Sauce{25%ml} and @Water for the Sauce{50%ml}.

Bring to a bubble and cook until the chicken is nicely coated. Remove from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Zest and halve the @Lime{1}(zested and halved).

Mix the coriander and a squeeze of lime juice through the stir-fry.

When the rice is cooked, fluff it up with a #fork{}. Mix in the lime zest. Taste and season with salt and black pepper if needed.

Chop the remaining lime into wedges.

Share the rice between your #bowls{} and spoon your sticky chicken on top.

Serve with a lime wedge for squeezing over. Enjoy!

> MOD Step 4: If you've added @King Prawns{150%g} to your meal, add them to the pan when you add the onion and pepper. IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.